creator: Foiti
descriptionHtml:
Foiti is a free social travel app with no ads or subscriptions. The core concept is to guide travellers to the place where the photo was precisely taken using geo-coordinates and find places within a radius where you have never been before.

The app is still in beta, but we are hopeful of building a stable version very soon. Some features are already available on the app but some are still under development.

Why did Foiti get created?

- Almost every photo capturing device has GPS other than a few DSLRs but when we see a photo online, we still can’t say where that photo was taken.

- We don’t have a go-to app for travelling.

- One writer writes about a place and we are left with no choice but to trust the writer.

- Worst thing is, we still can’t even find a place nearby to go for a drive.

These issues are still around us and there is no solution to them yet. Foiti is on the verge to change the way people travel and it is happening very soon.
descriptionShort: Social travel app to explore the world like it was suppose to be.
